---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="The Problem"
  description="Most B2B revenue problems aren't people problems — they're structural ones. Six taxes on your revenue journey that silently drain growth."
>
  <Nav />

  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#090e1a] pt-28 sm:pt-32 pb-16 sm:pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_320px] gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-end">
        <div>
          <p class="hero-eyebrow text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-white/30 uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-5">The Problem</p>
          <h1 class="hero-headline text-[36px] sm:text-[48px] md:text-[60px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-white leading-[1.05] max-w-3xl mb-6">
            Changing people<br />won't fix this.<br />
            <span class="text-white/35">Changing the structure will.</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="hero-sub text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-white/60 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            Most B2B revenue problems aren't execution problems. They're structural ones —
            gaps in how the revenue journey is designed. Six patterns show up again and again.
          </p>
        </div>
        <!-- Stat callout -->
        <div class="hero-ctas flex flex-col gap-3 pb-2">
          <div class="card-ring-dark rounded-[10px] px-5 sm:px-6 py-5">
            <div class="text-[32px] sm:text-[36px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-white leading-none mb-1">$3.5M</div>
            <div class="text-[12px] sm:text-[13px] text-white/40 leading-snug">Recovered in 6 months from one structural fix</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card-ring-dark rounded-[10px] px-5 sm:px-6 py-5">
            <div class="text-[32px] sm:text-[36px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-white leading-none mb-1">$84M</div>
            <div class="text-[13px] text-white/40 leading-snug">Scaled from $6M — same team, redesigned motion</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Blueprint Visual -->
  <section class="bg-[#090e1a] pb-12 sm:pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="rounded-[14px] overflow-hidden border border-white/[0.07]">
        <img
          src="/images/blueprint.png"
          alt="Revenue journey map showing structural leakage points at each stage"
          class="w-full block"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </div>
      <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] text-white/25 text-center mt-4 tracking-[0.04em]">
        The revenue journey mapped. Every drop is a structural gap — not a people problem.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Diagnostic Framing -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
        <div data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-[26px] sm:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] mb-6">
            The symptoms are visible.<br />The cause is structural.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-5">
            You hired strong people. You've invested in tools, in marketing, in sales process.
            And yet — the pipeline stalls, customers don't renew, growth plateaus.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-5">
            The instinct is to fix the people. Retrain the reps. Get better leads. Hire a VP.
            Sometimes that's right. But more often, the drag is structural — in how the revenue
            motion is designed, not in who's executing it.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
            Structural problems don't respond to execution pressure. They require structural fixes.
            And you can't fix what you haven't diagnosed.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-ring rounded-[12px] p-6 sm:p-8 bg-white" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="120">
          <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-5">Does this sound familiar?</p>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4">
            {[
              "Revenue is growing, but it's getting harder",
              "Pipeline looks healthy, close rates don't reflect it",
              "Good customers leave or don't expand",
              "New initiatives keep getting stuck at the same stage",
              "The team is working harder than the numbers suggest",
              "You've optimized the obvious things already",
              "Growth is there — but it feels fragile",
            ].map(item => (
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#f59e0b] mt-[7px] flex-shrink-0"></div>
                <span class="text-[13px] sm:text-[15px] text-[#4d4d4d]">{item}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Six Taxes Full Detail -->
  <section class="bg-[#fafafa] border-y border-black/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="mb-10 sm:mb-14" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-4">Root Causes</p>
        <h2 class="text-[28px] sm:text-[36px] md:text-[44px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] max-w-2xl mb-4">
          The Six Structural Taxes on your revenue
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
          These aren't symptoms. They're root causes — structural gaps in the revenue journey
          that silently tax every dollar of growth.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-5 sm:gap-6">
        {[
          {
            n: "01",
            icon: "broken-bridge",
            name: "The Broken Bridge",
            short: "Marketing and sales don't connect",
            body: "Marketing generates interest and passes leads. Sales doesn't know what to do with them — or doesn't trust them. The handoff is broken. Leads fall into a gap that nobody owns. The result: qualified interest never becomes pipeline. Marketing blames sales for not working leads. Sales blames marketing for bad leads. Both are probably right about the other — and wrong about the root cause.",
            signal: "High MQL volume, low SQL conversion"
          },
          {
            n: "02",
            icon: "leaky-bucket",
            name: "The Leaky Bucket",
            short: "Customers arrive but don't stay",
            body: "Acquisition is working. Retention isn't. You're investing heavily to fill the top of the bucket while it drains from the bottom. Churn destroys the compounding growth that should be happening. The worst part: many companies don't see this clearly because they're focused on new logo growth — while existing customers quietly leave.",
            signal: "New logo growth masking total revenue stagnation"
          },
          {
            n: "03",
            icon: "invisible-ceiling",
            name: "The Invisible Ceiling",
            short: "Growth stalls at the same threshold",
            body: "You hit $5M. Then you hit $5M again. You hire, you push, you invest — and you get back to $5M. The ceiling isn't the market. It's the infrastructure. Your go-to-market motion, your team design, your processes — they were built for where you were. Not for where you need to go. Until the structure changes, the ceiling stays.",
            signal: "Revenue plateau despite continued investment and effort"
          },
          {
            n: "04",
            icon: "expansion-gap",
            name: "The Expansion Gap",
            short: "Existing customers don't grow",
            body: "Your highest-margin revenue sits inside your current customer base. Most companies have no systematic motion to realize it — no expansion playbook, no CSM incentive to grow accounts, no product path to more value. The customers would expand. Nobody is engineering it. Net revenue retention below 100% is this tax in action.",
            signal: "NRR below 100%, no systematic expansion motion"
          },
          {
            n: "05",
            icon: "conversion-drag",
            name: "The Conversion Drag",
            short: "Pipeline moves slowly or stalls",
            body: "Qualified prospects exist. They engage. They go quiet. Or they keep saying 'almost' for six months. The problem isn't the prospect — it's the conversion architecture. The right content isn't surfacing at the right moment. The right stakeholders aren't being engaged. The decision support isn't there. Nobody built the motion to help buyers decide.",
            signal: "Long sales cycles, high late-stage drop rates"
          },
          {
            n: "06",
            icon: "misaligned-motion",
            name: "The Misaligned Motion",
            short: "Team effort doesn't compound",
            body: "Everyone is working. Marketing is optimizing for top-of-funnel. Sales is optimizing for this quarter's close. CS is trying to keep customers happy. None of it compounds because it's all optimized locally. Revenue journeys that hold are built when the whole motion is aligned — when each function reinforces the next. Without that, effort dissipates.",
            signal: "Inconsistent results, cross-functional friction, isolated wins"
          },
        ].map((tax, i) => (
          <div class="tax-card card-ring rounded-[10px] p-6 sm:p-8 bg-white" data-reveal data-reveal-delay={String(i * 60)}>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[200px_1fr] gap-6 sm:gap-8 items-start">
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                  <div class="icon-ring">
                    <Icon name={tax.icon} size={20} />
                  </div>
                  <span class="text-[11px] font-medium text-[#cccccc] font-mono">{tax.n}</span>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-[18px] sm:text-[22px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] text-[#171717] mb-1">{tax.name}</h3>
                <p class="text-[13px] sm:text-[14px] font-medium text-[#888888]">{tax.short}</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-[14px] sm:text-[15px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-5">{tax.body}</p>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 pt-4 border-t border-black/[0.06]">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#2563eb] flex-shrink-0"></div>
                  <span class="text-[12px] sm:text-[13px] text-[#888888]">Signal: {tax.signal}</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Cost -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-5">The Cost of Inaction</p>
        <h2 class="text-[28px] sm:text-[36px] md:text-[44px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] mb-6">
          These aren't small leaks
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-6">
          One company recovered $3.5M in six months by fixing their expansion gap.
          Another scaled from $6M to $84M by rebuilding the broken bridge and the invisible ceiling together.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-10">
          The structural taxes aren't rounding errors. They're compounding drags on
          every dollar of effort you're putting in. The longer they run, the more expensive they are.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/the-process"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3.5 bg-[#171717] text-white text-[14px] font-medium rounded-[6px] hover:bg-[#2a2a2a] transition-colors"
        >
          See how we fix it
          <Icon name="arrow-right" size={14} />
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
